Twilio SendGrid is a cloud-based email delivery platform that provides both an Email API for developers and a Marketing Campaigns suite for managing email marketing [1].

Authentication for the API is handled primarily via Bearer API keys [2]. SSO (SAML 2.0) is also supported for enterprise account management [3].

Access gates include free trials (no credit card required) [1], self-serve paid plans (Essentials, Pro, Premier), and custom pricing for high-volume or enterprise needs [1][4].

The API style is REST [2]. Developers may also utilize SMTP for email sending [4]. No official first-party MCP server was found.

Example API usage:

```javascript
const client = require("@sendgrid/client");
client.setApiKey(process.env.SENDGRID_API_KEY);

const request = {
  method: "PATCH",
  url: `/v3/teammates/${username}`,
  body: { is_admin: false, scopes: ["mail.send"] }
};

client.request(request);
```

Documentation: https://docs.sendgrid.com [4]

Firecrawl is an API service that converts websites into LLM-ready markdown or structured data [1][2].

Authentication for the cloud service uses API keys provided via a Bearer token in the Authorization header [1][3]. Users can sign up and manage keys through the Firecrawl dashboard or the CLI [1][3]. For specific agent environments, WorkOS ID-JAG registration is supported [1][4]. OAuth is also available for authenticating MCP clients [5]. A keyless free tier is available for limited usage via official clients (CLI, SDKs, or MCP) [1][3].

Firecrawl provides a REST API [1][3], a CLI for terminal-based operations [6][7], and an official MCP server [3][8]. Webhooks are supported for asynchronous processes like batch scraping [5]. Access is public; enterprise features and partner-specific API management are available via contact sales or official partnership pathways [5][2].

Official MCP Server:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "firecrawl": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "firecrawl-mcp"],
      "env": {
        "FIRECRAWL_API_KEY": "fc-YOUR-API-KEY"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
