Devin is an autonomous software engineering agent created by Cognition AI that plans, writes, tests, and deploys code within a sandboxed cloud environment.

Authentication and access are managed through the Devin dashboard, which typically supports SSO (GitHub or Google Workspace). Paid plans offer API access, requiring an API key generated by an admin. You can sign up or request access at https://devin.ai, with official documentation available at https://docs.devin.ai.

The platform provides a RESTful API and CLI for workflow automation. It supports webhooks for task status updates and integrates with third-party tools via an official Model Context Protocol (MCP) server.

```javascript
// Minimal API usage example
const client = new DevinClient(api_key);
const session = client.create_session(model="devin-v3-enterprise");
session.start_task({ instructions: "Refactor auth module", repository: "org/repo" });
```
